In. No?
- Mm.

01:10:14.464 --> 01:10:16.049
- All right.

01:10:25.726 --> 01:10:28.395
[soft dramatic music]

01:10:28.437 --> 01:10:31.648
- One form of arthritis
may be caused by a germ

01:10:31.690 --> 01:10:34.693
or virus that's being
transmitted by ticks,

01:10:34.735 --> 01:10:37.362
the insects that thrive
in wooded areas.

01:10:37.404 --> 01:10:38.864
The research could,
at the same time,

01:10:38.906 --> 01:10:40.407
in the distant future,

01:10:40.449 --> 01:10:42.159
lead to the development
of a vaccine

01:10:42.201 --> 01:10:43.952
against this one form
of arthritis,

01:10:43.994 --> 01:10:45.954
which is being called
Lyme arthritis.

01:10:52.085 --> 01:10:56.340
- Around 1980, a law called
Bayh-Dole was passed.

01:10:57.549 --> 01:10:59.675
Bayh-Dole changed
the patent law

01:10:59.718 --> 01:11:04.306
to make it permissible
for grantees of federal funds

01:11:04.348 --> 01:11:07.601
and also some of the federal
agencies themselves

01:11:07.643 --> 01:11:11.063
to benefit from patents
that were acquired.

01:11:11.980 --> 01:11:13.565
- This set the stage

01:11:13.607 --> 01:11:15.317
for people who had,
at one time,

01:11:15.359 --> 01:11:17.193
been just pure scientists

01:11:17.236 --> 01:11:21.365
to actually make money
from their research.

01:11:21.406 --> 01:11:24.785
And it set the stage
for some pretty concerning

01:11:24.826 --> 01:11:27.079
conflicts of interest.

01:11:27.120 --> 01:11:29.206
- So--okay, this is 1980.

01:11:29.248 --> 01:11:30.541
So guess what.

01:11:30.582 --> 01:11:36.171
1982, that's when the Borrelia
organism was discovered.

01:11:37.464 --> 01:11:40.342
A, the Lyme organism
is arguably one

01:11:40.384 --> 01:11:43.554
of the most complex bacteria
known to man,

01:11:43.594 --> 01:11:47.599
and, B, arguably
or maybe inarguably,

01:11:47.641 --> 01:11:50.769
it is the most heavily patented
bacteria known to man.

01:11:50.811 --> 01:11:53.772
[tense music]

01:11:53.814 --> 01:11:56.733
♪ ♪

01:11:56.775 --> 01:11:59.027
So everybody has a piece
of this bacteria.

01:12:01.697 --> 01:12:03.782
- A study out tonight
concludes lab tests

01:12:03.824 --> 01:12:06.785
for Lyme disease
are strikingly inaccurate.

01:12:06.827 --> 01:12:09.288
Experts say tests made
by more than 30 companies

01:12:09.329 --> 01:12:12.666
who jumped into the business
are just not very good.

01:12:12.708 --> 01:12:16.003
The government is now pumping money
into developing a better blood test--

01:12:16.044 --> 01:12:17.421
a little late, experts say,

01:12:17.462 --> 01:12:20.174
but a recognition that what was
once a regional problem

01:12:20.215 --> 01:12:21.508
is now a national one.

01:12:22.300 --> 01:12:25.304
- So in 1994,

01:12:25.344 --> 01:12:29.516
the major players in the NIH,
in the CDC,

01:12:29.558 --> 01:12:33.103
and the IDSA
came together for a conference

01:12:33.145 --> 01:12:38.150
in Dearborn, Michigan,
to develop a standard test.

01:12:38.192 --> 01:12:41.403
But the huge backdrop
was a vaccine.

01:12:41.445 --> 01:12:44.072
A vaccine was in development.

01:12:44.114 --> 01:12:49.827
And it would affect the way
this test was constructed.

01:12:52.748 --> 01:12:56.126
- A Western blot is a test
where they actually take a blotter,

01:12:56.168 --> 01:12:58.921
and on this blotter,
they take a drop of your blood

01:12:58.962 --> 01:13:00.464
or your serum,
and they put it on the blot,

01:13:00.505 --> 01:13:03.300
and it starts to move;
it migrates.

01:13:03.342 --> 01:13:06.929
The bacteria has proteins
on the outside of its surface,

01:13:06.969 --> 01:13:11.808
and your immune system recognizes
some of these specific proteins.

01:13:11.850 --> 01:13:13.809
It's like a lock and a key.

01:13:13.852 --> 01:13:16.355
If you have five
of these specific proteins

01:13:16.396 --> 01:13:18.357
that show you've been
exposed to Lyme,

01:13:18.398 --> 01:13:21.401
you have a CDC positive
Western blot.

01:13:21.443 --> 01:13:25.405
- But what these powers
of Lyme disease decided to do

01:13:25.447 --> 01:13:29.034
was to eliminate
two of those key markers,

01:13:29.076 --> 01:13:30.994
because they were going
to be used

01:13:31.036 --> 01:13:34.121
in the development
of a vaccine.

01:13:34.164 --> 01:13:37.000
Those two markers
would be used

01:13:37.041 --> 01:13:41.171
to spur the antibody response
when you got the vaccine.

01:13:41.213 --> 01:13:45.175
So they decided they needed
to remove them from the test

01:13:45.217 --> 01:13:48.136
so that if you had been vaccinated,

01:13:48.178 --> 01:13:51.849
you would not test positive
for Lyme disease.

01:13:51.889 --> 01:13:53.517
- Now, why is that important?

01:13:53.559 --> 01:13:56.562
When you take away
the 31 and 34 bands,

01:13:56.603 --> 01:13:58.897
which are highly specific
for Lyme,

01:13:58.939 --> 01:14:00.816
you're then taking away
the possibility

01:14:00.858 --> 01:14:03.402
for those people
who've not had the vaccine

01:14:03.443 --> 01:14:05.737
to help diagnose this disease.

01:14:05.779 --> 01:14:07.656
So if you come
to a doctor's office,

01:14:07.698 --> 01:14:10.534
"Doc, I got a swollen knee.
I can't walk. I'm tired.

01:14:10.576 --> 01:14:13.161
My memory's not working.
I've seen 20 doctors,"

01:14:13.202 --> 01:14:15.371
and they bring
in their Western blot

01:14:15.414 --> 01:14:17.583
and they've got four
out of five bands,

01:14:17.624 --> 01:14:21.128
but your fifth band happens
to be the 31 or 34,

01:14:21.170 --> 01:14:23.755
they would call that
a CDC negative Western blot,

01:14:23.797 --> 01:14:25.966
yet you have Lyme disease.

01:14:29.303 --> 01:14:30.846
- There is a vaccine,

01:14:30.888 --> 01:14:35.434
but now there are reports
of serious side effects.

01:14:37.477 --> 01:14:40.564
- By the late 1990s,
there were two companies

01:14:40.606 --> 01:14:44.318
making two competing vaccines
that were almost identical.

01:14:44.359 --> 01:14:47.404
One of them got mired
in lawsuits

01:14:47.446 --> 01:14:49.573
because people claimed
there were side effects,

01:14:49.615 --> 01:14:54.870
and it was pulled from the market,
leaving only LYMErix.

01:14:54.912 --> 01:14:57.080
There were a lot of unanswered
questions about LYMErix.

01:14:57.121 --> 01:14:59.666
The FDA panel that passed it,

01:14:59.708 --> 01:15:02.252
they said that there are
a lot of unknowns here,

01:15:02.294 --> 01:15:05.088
but they were passing it
through anyway.

01:15:05.130 --> 01:15:08.675
- The safety issue here seems
to me to be very complicated

01:15:08.717 --> 01:15:11.553
compared to any vaccine I know
that has been licensed.

01:15:11.594 --> 01:15:13.388
Those who did the trial
have unearthed

01:15:13.430 --> 01:15:16.225
some very interesting,
sinister possibilities

01:15:16.266 --> 01:15:18.143
that may or may not be real.

01:15:18.184 --> 01:15:22.147
And as I said earlier,
rare events will become common

01:15:22.189 --> 01:15:25.025
when a million people
are vaccinated.

01:15:25.067 --> 01:15:27.528
- I might comment that this
is fairly rare for a vaccine

01:15:27.568 --> 01:15:30.112
to be voted on
with so much ambivalence.

01:15:30.155 --> 01:15:32.907
So that is all
for the formal vote.

01:15:34.117 --> 01:15:35.869
- In the years
since it's been on the market,

01:15:35.911 --> 01:15:37.621
600,000 people have taken it.

01:15:37.663 --> 01:15:42.501
Nearly 300 adverse reactions
have been reported to the FDA.

01:15:42.543 --> 01:15:45.170
- Panel of experts
that advises the FDA

01:15:45.212 --> 01:15:47.673
found the story so compelling
that it asked the agency

01:15:47.714 --> 01:15:50.008
to carry out
a large-scale investigation

01:15:50.050 --> 01:15:52.344
of possible harmful effects
of the vaccine.

01:15:52.386 --> 01:15:55.681
- There was a meeting at FDA.

01:15:55.722 --> 01:15:59.101
I was actually invited
to go to that meeting.

01:15:59.142 --> 01:16:01.645
The star witness
at this FDA meeting

01:16:01.687 --> 01:16:06.066
was the chief scientist
for the Connaught vaccine.

01:16:06.108 --> 01:16:09.027
So you got it? Like--like, there was
Glaxo and Connaught.

01:16:09.068 --> 01:16:11.029
Connaught pulled out.

01:16:11.071 --> 01:16:14.782
He said, "Since LYMErix
has been given out

01:16:14.825 --> 01:16:17.160
"to so many people,

01:16:17.202 --> 01:16:21.707
"we can see that there are
some very severe side effects.

01:16:21.748 --> 01:16:24.751
"These are not
common side effects,

01:16:24.793 --> 01:16:28.046
"but some of them
are very bad,

01:16:28.088 --> 01:16:31.341
"and I would never recommend
vaccinating people

01:16:31.383 --> 01:16:33.677
with this vaccine."

01:16:33.719 --> 01:16:36.180
- There is no such thing
as a perfect vaccine.

01:16:36.221 --> 01:16:40.017
What we can say is that
this vaccine is very effective,

01:16:40.058 --> 01:16:42.936
and it's very well-tolerated.

01:16:42.978 --> 01:16:44.271
- It's been a nightmare.

01:16:44.313 --> 01:16:48.483
Prior to this, I was hunting,
fishing, hiking.

01:16:48.525 --> 01:16:51.528
- How much has it
changed your life?

01:16:51.570 --> 01:16:54.948
- I don't have a life anymore.

01:16:57.451 --> 01:17:00.579
- In April, the manufacturer
of a Lyme disease vaccine

01:17:00.621 --> 01:17:03.248
took it off the market,
citing poor sales

01:17:03.290 --> 01:17:06.627
following unproven allegations
of side effects.

01:17:07.835 --> 01:17:11.423
- The vaccine was taken
off the market in 2002.

01:17:12.549 --> 01:17:16.553
We have not had a Lyme disease
vaccine for 20 years,

01:17:16.594 --> 01:17:20.557
and yet those two markers
were not restored to the test.

01:17:22.851 --> 01:17:25.812
If you were bitten
by a tick tomorrow,

01:17:25.853 --> 01:17:29.858
this is the test that would be used
to diagnose you.

01:17:33.820 --> 01:17:37.032
Many people have
invested their careers

01:17:37.074 --> 01:17:40.994
in this model of Lyme disease:

01:17:41.036 --> 01:17:46.041
it's easy to diagnose,
it's straightforward to cure.

01:17:46.083 --> 01:17:49.419
And that is the story
that prevails today.

01:17:50.838 --> 01:17:54.007
But it's far different
from where we started.

01:17:54.049 --> 01:17:56.927
[building dramatic music]

01:17:56.969 --> 01:18:03.976
♪ ♪

01:18:08.272 --> 01:18:11.650
In the beginning,
there was openness.

01:18:11.692 --> 01:18:15.279
There was willingness
to consider lots of possibilities.

01:18:16.446 --> 01:18:19.950
But over time, doors closed.

01:18:21.159 --> 01:18:22.702
When I went back and looked

01:18:22.744 --> 01:18:26.582
at some of the early
scientific literature,

01:18:26.623 --> 01:18:30.043
I found a sort
of familiar illness.

01:18:31.962 --> 01:18:35.382
So I'm just going
to read from a 1994 letter

01:18:35.424 --> 01:18:37.925
by Allen Steere.

01:18:37.968 --> 01:18:40.137
"It has become
increasingly apparent

01:18:40.179 --> 01:18:42.014
"that the Lyme disease
spirochete,

01:18:42.055 --> 01:18:43.639
"Borrelia burgdorferi,

01:18:43.682 --> 01:18:47.186
"may persist
in some patients for years.

01:18:47.227 --> 01:18:50.230
"Of particular concern,
recent studies have shown

01:18:50.272 --> 01:18:53.192
"that the spirochete may persist
in the nervous system

01:18:53.233 --> 01:18:57.612
and may cause chronic
neurologic involvement."

01:18:57.654 --> 01:19:01.532
The word "chronic"
is there a couple of times.

01:19:01.575 --> 01:19:05.329
- Some of the authors who have
signed on to those guidelines,

01:19:05.370 --> 01:19:06.996
if you look
at their published work

01:19:07.039 --> 01:19:09.666
from the late '80s
and early '90s,

01:19:09.708 --> 01:19:14.630
their words say exactly
what we say--chronic.

01:19:14.671 --> 01:19:17.216
- Once you get Lyme disease,
your body's immune system

01:19:17.257 --> 01:19:19.092
doesn't deal with it terribly well.

01:19:19.134 --> 01:19:21.719
It doesn't clear
that spirochete from your body,

01:19:21.762 --> 01:19:25.139
and you can be infected
for virtually forever.

01:19:25.182 --> 01:19:27.351
- And it's
a very scary disease.

01:19:27.392 --> 01:19:28.769
- It doesn't really
have to be.

01:19:28.809 --> 01:19:31.980
I think it's overemphasized
how bad it can be.

01:19:32.022 --> 01:19:34.233
With prompt treatment
and recognition,

01:19:34.273 --> 01:19:35.984
it's not a big deal.

01:19:37.443 --> 01:19:40.364
- Another concept
that has been more or less

01:19:40.405 --> 01:19:43.367
brushed aside
is whether a mother

01:19:43.407 --> 01:19:47.037
can pass Lyme disease
on to her unborn baby.

01:19:47.079 --> 01:19:50.040
- It was a dramatic
and frightening new development:

01:19:50.082 --> 01:19:51.875
the germ that causes Lyme

01:19:51.916 --> 01:19:54.169
can also travel
through the placenta.

01:19:54.210 --> 01:19:55.838
- On occasion,
a pregnant woman

01:19:55.879 --> 01:19:57.880
has been able
to transmit the illness

01:19:57.923 --> 01:20:01.635
to the developing child
in the uterus.

01:20:01.677 --> 01:20:03.846
This may have
serious complications

01:20:03.887 --> 01:20:05.806
for the developing child.

01:20:05.848 --> 01:20:08.934
We don't know how frequently
this happens at this point,

01:20:08.976 --> 01:20:11.895
but it is something
that we are concerned about.

01:20:11.937 --> 01:20:14.857
- They did autopsies
on these babies

01:20:14.898 --> 01:20:17.609
and found spirochetes
in their tissues,

01:20:17.651 --> 01:20:20.445
in their hearts,
in their lungs.

01:20:20.487 --> 01:20:23.448
This was solid science.

01:20:23.490 --> 01:20:26.660
But it became something
that was dismissed

01:20:26.702 --> 01:20:29.663
in the mainstream literature
and practice.

01:20:30.789 --> 01:20:34.751
They used to acknowledge
that chronic Lyme disease was real.

01:20:34.793 --> 01:20:37.963
They used to acknowledge
congenital Lyme disease.

01:20:38.755 --> 01:20:40.382
- But at a certain point
in time,

01:20:40.424 --> 01:20:43.218
that became dogma,
that there's no such thing

01:20:43.260 --> 01:20:45.179
as chronic Lyme disease, period.

01:20:45.219 --> 01:20:47.306
End of story.

01:20:47.347 --> 01:20:49.850
In order to qualify a vaccine,

01:20:49.892 --> 01:20:53.478
it's much more helpful to have
a fairly simplistic model,

01:20:53.520 --> 01:20:56.190
where you can easily tell
who has the disease

01:20:56.231 --> 01:20:58.358
and who doesn't
have the disease.

01:20:58.400 --> 01:21:02.612
And furthermore, you banish
the notion that the infection

01:21:02.654 --> 01:21:06.407
can persist despite
application of treatment.

01:21:06.450 --> 01:21:09.912
If you acknowledge
those biologic realities,

01:21:09.952 --> 01:21:12.581
it makes it considerably
more difficult

01:21:12.623 --> 01:21:14.291
to qualify a vaccine.

01:21:23.425 --> 01:21:26.637
- After years of research,
it begs the question,

01:21:26.678 --> 01:21:29.514
why is there still
no vaccine people can get

01:21:29.556 --> 01:21:31.975
to prevent Lyme disease?

01:21:32.017 --> 01:21:33.184
- I think the time has come

01:21:33.227 --> 01:21:36.396
to reconsider the decision.

01:21:36.438 --> 01:21:39.608
Lyme disease is the only
infection that I know of

01:21:39.650 --> 01:21:42.486
for which
there is an effective vaccine,

01:21:42.528 --> 01:21:45.531
but it's not available
to the public.

01:21:46.698 --> 01:21:48.700
- And in fact,
the French biotech firm

01:21:48.742 --> 01:21:52.037
Valneva
is testing a new vaccine

01:21:52.079 --> 01:21:54.248
that is similar to LYMErix.

01:21:54.289 --> 01:21:55.749
- Is this vaccine based

01:21:55.791 --> 01:21:58.043
on different medicine
than the old one?

01:21:58.085 --> 01:22:00.754
- No, actually, it's quite similar
to the old vaccine.

01:22:00.796 --> 01:22:02.339
They did change it
a little bit.

01:22:02.380 --> 01:22:04.550
They removed a protein
which they thought

01:22:04.591 --> 01:22:06.343
may have been causing
some health problems.

01:22:06.385 --> 01:22:09.096
But we now know
that the old vaccine

01:22:09.137 --> 01:22:11.557
actually doesn't cause
any health problems.

01:22:11.598 --> 01:22:14.559
[inquisitive music]

01:22:14.601 --> 01:22:15.894
♪ ♪

01:22:15.936 --> 01:22:17.938
- There are so many
conspiracy theories

01:22:17.980 --> 01:22:19.606
swirling around the public,

01:22:19.648 --> 01:22:21.817
like the anti-vaxxers, right?

01:22:23.360 --> 01:22:26.446
And I think what happens
with Lyme disease

01:22:26.487 --> 01:22:29.867
is that it gets swept up
into all of that,

01:22:29.907 --> 01:22:33.036
when in fact,
in this situation,

01:22:33.077 --> 01:22:36.290
we're not talking
about a conspiracy.

01:22:37.249 --> 01:22:41.420
We're talking
about flawed science,

01:22:41.460 --> 01:22:43.880
science that has
been reinvented

01:22:43.922 --> 01:22:46.633
to facilitate products.

01:22:48.594 --> 01:22:52.097
- It would be great
if we had a vaccine

01:22:52.139 --> 01:22:54.516
that was effective and safe.

01:22:54.558 --> 01:22:58.437
But that's not gonna solve
our problem of ticks.

01:22:58.478 --> 01:23:01.440
And moreover, we can protect
ourselves from Lyme disease,

01:23:01.481 --> 01:23:05.318
but there's other things,
as we know, in ticks.

01:23:05.360 --> 01:23:09.865
We need a vaccine that would
attack all of these illnesses.

01:23:09.907 --> 01:23:15.412
An anti-tick vaccine really
would be the ideal approach.

01:23:15.454 --> 01:23:19.625
But beyond that, we have
this other elephant in the room.

01:23:19.666 --> 01:23:22.544
We have the many, many people,

01:23:22.585 --> 01:23:26.632
year after year,
who remain sick.

01:23:28.467 --> 01:23:31.136
- This is a hard problem.

01:23:31.178 --> 01:23:33.680
The way to resolve it,

01:23:33.722 --> 01:23:37.518
it's not to make everything
so simple and so cut and dry.

01:23:37.559 --> 01:23:41.188
It is to really look
at the nuance.

01:23:41.230 --> 01:23:42.981
I really did come to believe,

01:23:43.023 --> 01:23:45.943
after all of this research
and investigation,

01:23:45.984 --> 01:23:50.656
that the definition of Lyme disease
had been twisted

01:23:50.697 --> 01:23:54.952
to accommodate the passage
of that vaccine.

01:23:54.993 --> 01:23:57.162
It was a business interest.

01:23:57.204 --> 01:24:00.999
It was a rationalization
in the interest of a product

01:24:01.041 --> 01:24:03.043
but not the patient.

01:24:15.931 --> 01:24:17.391
[elevator bell dings]

01:24:19.518 --> 01:24:22.521
[indistinct chatter]

01:24:30.571 --> 01:24:33.866
- I want you to look at that.
- Yeah.

01:24:33.907 --> 01:24:35.951
- This is your brain stem.
- Yes.

01:24:35.993 --> 01:24:39.746
- This is responsible
for balance,

01:24:39.788 --> 01:24:43.541
for swallowing, for breathing,
for heart rate.

01:24:44.751 --> 01:24:47.462
This very tip of the brain
right here

01:24:47.504 --> 01:24:49.255
is your motor strip.

01:24:49.298 --> 01:24:51.758
It starts with your hips
and your legs.

01:24:54.344 --> 01:24:57.139
Okay.
So look.

01:24:59.141 --> 01:25:01.059
Gray.
- Yeah.

01:25:01.101 --> 01:25:03.896
- Orange, purple, white,
that's healthy.

01:25:03.937 --> 01:25:07.773
- Okay.
- These colors are damaged.

01:25:07.816 --> 01:25:09.985
Number five is black.

01:25:10.027 --> 01:25:12.279
- Yeah.
- See the black?

01:25:12.321 --> 01:25:14.615
You have a lot
of damage to it.

01:25:14.656 --> 01:25:17.534
You can't even see
your brain stem.

01:25:17.576 --> 01:25:21.079
Your brain stem
is completely black.

01:25:21.121 --> 01:25:26.710
Your motor strip,
sensory, all black.

01:25:26.752 --> 01:25:28.420
That's why you can't
move your legs.

01:25:28.462 --> 01:25:30.589
That's why you can't
feel your legs.

01:25:32.966 --> 01:25:34.968
[choking up]
You have your answer today.

01:25:36.844 --> 01:25:38.514
- So I'm not going crazy?

01:25:38.555 --> 01:25:40.516
- You're not going crazy.

01:25:44.811 --> 01:25:47.189
Dr. Shroff said

01:25:47.231 --> 01:25:52.736
that without treatment for Lyme,
this gets worse,

01:25:52.778 --> 01:25:56.031
and pretty soon,
you would have lost everything.

01:25:58.075 --> 01:26:01.827
Three years of treatment,
and I keep questioning myself

01:26:01.870 --> 01:26:04.665
if I'm doing the right thing.

01:26:04.706 --> 01:26:06.625
We've been doing
the right thing.

01:26:06.666 --> 01:26:08.460
We've been keeping it at bay.

01:26:08.502 --> 01:26:11.463
What did you tell me today
during your MRI?

01:26:11.505 --> 01:26:13.549
You said, "Why do we have
to do this again?

01:26:13.590 --> 01:26:15.550
They're not gonna find anything."

01:26:15.592 --> 01:26:17.511
See? You found something.

01:26:17.553 --> 01:26:20.514
This is why you have
the issues you have.

01:26:20.556 --> 01:26:22.349
Look. They're right there.

01:26:22.391 --> 01:26:23.392
That's damage.

01:26:25.686 --> 01:26:27.437
You're not going crazy.

01:26:27.478 --> 01:26:30.440
[tense music]

01:26:30.482 --> 01:26:37.489
♪ ♪

01:26:46.331 --> 01:26:49.293
[somber music]

01:26:49.334 --> 01:26:52.087
♪ ♪

01:26:52.129 --> 01:26:54.380
Julia and I initially were
supposed to be in India

01:26:54.423 --> 01:26:55.591
for three months.

01:26:59.178 --> 01:27:02.806
But the clinic shut down,
and we were forced to leave.

01:27:08.853 --> 01:27:10.647
Unfortunately,
the stem cells really didn't

01:27:10.689 --> 01:27:12.773
change that much.

01:27:12.816 --> 01:27:14.359
A lot of letdowns.

01:27:14.401 --> 01:27:16.820
But if we want
to get Julia better,

01:27:16.862 --> 01:27:19.323
we have to give trust.

01:27:19.364 --> 01:27:20.782
We have to try.

01:27:20.824 --> 01:27:23.785
[hopeful music]

01:27:23.827 --> 01:27:26.746
♪ ♪

01:27:26.788 --> 01:27:29.458
We long for her to walk.

01:27:29.499 --> 01:27:31.919
[indistinct chatter]

01:27:31.960 --> 01:27:34.254
I would like to see her dance
with her friends.

01:27:34.296 --> 01:27:35.923
I'd like to dance with her.

01:27:38.133 --> 01:27:42.888
It's the simplest things that
we take for granted every day

01:27:42.930 --> 01:27:45.474
that I pray for with Julia.

01:27:45.516 --> 01:27:47.809
- My legs hurt.

01:27:47.851 --> 01:27:49.686
- But we'll get there.
[sniffles]

01:27:49.728 --> 01:27:51.438
We'll get there slowly.

01:27:51.480 --> 01:27:53.857
And I think
when we do get there,

01:27:53.898 --> 01:27:56.235
it's gonna be very rewarding.

01:28:04.243 --> 01:28:07.246
[indistinct chatter]

01:28:10.749 --> 01:28:12.918
- Let's have a round
of applause once again

01:28:12.960 --> 01:28:14.545
for Julia Rose.

01:28:14.585 --> 01:28:17.965
[cheers and applause]

01:28:18.005 --> 01:28:20.592
- The 16th candle,
I've been told,

01:28:20.634 --> 01:28:24.847
is for your greatest love,
or even your hero.

01:28:24.888 --> 01:28:28.642
When I thought about
who that one person was,

01:28:28.684 --> 01:28:31.019
one person came to mind.

01:28:31.061 --> 01:28:33.230
And that was you, Dad.

01:28:34.898 --> 01:28:38.568
Dad, the greatest doctors
in the world

01:28:38.610 --> 01:28:41.737
weren't able to figure out
what was wrong with me,

01:28:41.780 --> 01:28:44.074
but you were.

01:28:44.116 --> 01:28:47.536
Without you, I'm afraid
I wouldn't be here today,

01:28:47.577 --> 01:28:49.955
giving you guys a speech.

01:28:49.996 --> 01:28:52.583
[cheers and applause]

01:28:52.624 --> 01:28:57.045
Thank you for holding my hand
through every blood test,

01:28:57.087 --> 01:28:58.964
every scary procedure,

01:28:59.005 --> 01:29:01.508
and every single hard time.

01:29:02.759 --> 01:29:05.387
You are my hero,
my greatest love,

01:29:05.429 --> 01:29:07.681
and my biggest inspiration.

01:29:10.726 --> 01:29:13.937
My idea of a miracle
has definitely changed.

01:29:13.978 --> 01:29:16.273
- Holy Father!

01:29:16.315 --> 01:29:18.442
- That day,
I asked for a miracle,

01:29:18.483 --> 01:29:21.904
and my miracle, in my mind,
was getting up from the chair

01:29:21.945 --> 01:29:23.655
and walking
and going back to that life

01:29:23.697 --> 01:29:27.951
of normalcy and dancing, and--
and it is still.

01:29:27.993 --> 01:29:30.495
That's--you know,
that would be a miracle.

01:29:30.537 --> 01:29:32.414
But I think miracles
happen every day.

01:29:32.456 --> 01:29:35.584
I think that me sitting here
talking to you is a miracle.

01:29:36.502 --> 01:29:38.629
What happened to me
and the reaching out

01:29:38.670 --> 01:29:41.130
and the love,
that's a miracle.

01:29:41.173 --> 01:29:43.133
[applause]

01:29:43.175 --> 01:29:45.636
And I think
we don't even realize it.

01:29:45.677 --> 01:29:49.223
The little things every day
that we have are miracles.

01:29:50.516 --> 01:29:53.852
all: ♪ Hey, baby, ooh, ah ♪

01:29:53.894 --> 01:29:55.687
♪ I want to know ♪

01:29:59.900 --> 01:30:02.693
[cheers and applause]

01:30:06.406 --> 01:30:08.700
- It's funny, people ask me
all the time,

01:30:08.742 --> 01:30:13.830
"Are you angry that you
weren't diagnosed early on

01:30:13.871 --> 01:30:16.750
and you could have
avoided all of this?"

01:30:18.710 --> 01:30:22.880
And I tell them
I'm actually not angry.

01:30:28.344 --> 01:30:31.974
I would certainly never wish
what I went through on anyone.

01:30:32.014 --> 01:30:33.517
But, you know, in some sense,

01:30:33.559 --> 01:30:37.103
I feel like it was part
of the bigger plan for me.

01:30:39.940 --> 01:30:43.777
Wasn't always pleasant,
but you know what?

01:30:43.818 --> 01:30:47.155
There's been so many good things
about what I've gone through.

01:30:54.580 --> 01:30:58.375
Whether I live five hours,
five days,

01:30:58.416 --> 01:31:00.835
50 months, or 50 years,

01:31:00.878 --> 01:31:03.213
it's got to be,
like, a fulfilling life.

01:31:04.590 --> 01:31:10.262
I mean, I can't look back
and regret not having done things.

01:31:10.304 --> 01:31:13.264
[atmospheric music]

01:31:13.307 --> 01:31:19.228
♪ ♪

01:31:25.943 --> 01:31:29.156
Happy belated New Year.

01:31:29.198 --> 01:31:30.949
People have asked me
if everything's okay.

01:31:30.991 --> 01:31:32.534
They hadn't heard from me
in a while.

01:31:32.576 --> 01:31:35.996
And I just wanted
to send this message.

01:31:36.038 --> 01:31:38.165
You know, I may look tired.
I am pretty tired.

01:31:38.207 --> 01:31:43.295
I think I need to conserve
my energy for the push ahead.

01:31:45.672 --> 01:31:48.175
I made a promise to all of you

01:31:48.217 --> 01:31:51.929
that I would continue
to work tirelessly.

01:31:51.969 --> 01:31:54.473
I will continue to honor
that promise,

01:31:54.514 --> 01:31:56.558
and my thoughts and prayers
are with all of you.

01:31:56.600 --> 01:31:58.227
So take care.

01:31:58.268 --> 01:32:01.230
[soft dramatic music]

01:32:01.271 --> 01:32:08.278
♪ ♪

01:32:25.212 --> 01:32:28.257
I've taken care of people
at the prime of their lives,

01:32:28.298 --> 01:32:30.425
great jobs,
beautiful families,

01:32:30.467 --> 01:32:32.052
devastating cancers.

01:32:32.094 --> 01:32:34.429
Like, "Why did this
happen to me?"

01:32:34.471 --> 01:32:36.223
I mean,
that's the universal question,

01:32:36.264 --> 01:32:38.100
"Why did this happen to me?"

01:32:40.102 --> 01:32:43.313
My grandmother used to say to me,
"Why not you?

01:32:43.355 --> 01:32:45.023
Why shouldn't it happen
to you?"

01:32:48.110 --> 01:32:51.362
The question is not, "Why?"
but, "How do you move beyond it?"

01:33:22.644 --> 01:33:26.356
[hopeful music]

01:33:26.398 --> 01:33:28.442
- I think about the people
who have died

01:33:28.483 --> 01:33:30.235
and that are dying

01:33:30.277 --> 01:33:34.114
and the people who are alone,
and I feel very guilty,

01:33:34.156 --> 01:33:36.325
because I'm getting
all this help,

01:33:36.366 --> 01:33:38.243
and these people
need help too.

01:33:39.702 --> 01:33:41.830
I feel like I'm obligated
to do this

01:33:41.871 --> 01:33:45.375
and that this needs to happen
in order for there to be a change.

01:33:46.919 --> 01:33:49.546
I was a different person
before Lyme,

01:33:49.588 --> 01:33:51.715
a normal girl.

01:33:51.757 --> 01:33:54.425
Now is the time for action.

01:33:54.468 --> 01:33:57.387
We must stand together as one.

01:33:57.429 --> 01:33:59.889
For the people
suffering right now,

01:33:59.932 --> 01:34:02.643
let us be their voice.

01:34:02.684 --> 01:34:04.978
For the people we have lost,

01:34:05.020 --> 01:34:08.232
let us grieve them
and fight in their memory.

01:34:08.273 --> 01:34:10.234
I'm determined
to bring about change,

01:34:10.275 --> 01:34:13.445
and I trust that together,
we can bring hope

01:34:13.487 --> 01:34:16.031
to those who have forgotten
the meaning of the word.

01:34:19.243 --> 01:34:22.037
My mind is there,
but my body isn't yet.

01:34:22.079 --> 01:34:24.414
But I'm determined,
even if I am in a wheelchair

01:34:24.456 --> 01:34:27.334
and I am sick,

01:34:27.376 --> 01:34:29.837
I want to help more people.

01:34:45.143 --> 01:34:46.687
- You can't give up.

01:34:46.728 --> 01:34:48.897
Because if it was you,
your family,

01:34:48.939 --> 01:34:52.901
you can't just turn people away
and say there's no hope.

01:34:52.943 --> 01:34:54.820
People are contacting me
all the time,

01:34:54.862 --> 01:34:56.822
from all over the world.

01:34:58.657 --> 01:35:00.157
I need to share
this information

01:35:00.200 --> 01:35:02.244
because this
is a worldwide epidemic.

01:35:03.327 --> 01:35:05.664
- The whole world
is in disastrous situation

01:35:05.706 --> 01:35:08.709
because of the position

01:35:08.750 --> 01:35:10.460
of a small group of experts

01:35:10.502 --> 01:35:12.004
at the IDSA

01:35:12.045 --> 01:35:13.255
in the United States
of America,

01:35:13.297 --> 01:35:16.175
because they made
recommendations,

01:35:16.216 --> 01:35:19.594
and it was imposed
to the whole world.

01:35:21.889 --> 01:35:27.186
- So here we are in the midst
of a huge epidemic.

01:35:27.227 --> 01:35:29.688
We've all come
to an understanding

01:35:29.730 --> 01:35:33.066
of what this can mean
in our everyday lives.

01:35:34.318 --> 01:35:37.029
In the case of COVID,
we are accepting

01:35:37.070 --> 01:35:40.157
that there is something
called long-haul.

01:35:40.199 --> 01:35:44.494
The difference is,
they are being taken seriously.

01:35:44.536 --> 01:35:48.457
But Lyme disease has been
this quiet epidemic

01:35:48.498 --> 01:35:50.334
for decades.

01:35:52.710 --> 01:35:57.382
We all have to realize
that we're at risk.

01:35:57.424 --> 01:36:02.387
This is a growing
and common threat.

01:36:03.764 --> 01:36:05.599
And yet for too long,

01:36:05.641 --> 01:36:07.809
the problem
has been minimized.

01:36:09.561 --> 01:36:15.651
Settling this debate is going
to require new researchers,

01:36:15.692 --> 01:36:17.361
new science.

01:36:18.820 --> 01:36:22.115
We need new ideas
about Lyme disease

01:36:22.157 --> 01:36:24.493
and people who are willing...

01:36:26.870 --> 01:36:29.456
To challenge the old guard.

01:37:32.436 --> 01:37:35.272
- Right by my tweezer,
that's a larva,

01:37:35.314 --> 01:37:37.191
and it's fully engorged.

01:37:37.232 --> 01:37:40.027
It's probably going
to drop off today.

01:37:40.068 --> 01:37:42.237
The fully engorged larvae
look like poppy seeds.

01:37:42.279 --> 01:37:44.781
One larva, right ear.
One larva, left ear.

01:37:57.878 --> 01:38:01.048
- We have an early warning
in your health this morning.

01:38:01.089 --> 01:38:06.469
- Scientists predict this could be
the worst Lyme disease season in years.
